1.00	Ramkishan_Adig	Ramkishan Adig	Ramkishan Adig (born August 7, 1967) is one of the most important Indian artists and also a prominent and influential practitioner of The Social-Realism style in painting.Born of a small village in Rajasthan , studied art at Rajasthan school of Art, Jaipur. In 1996 his poster awarded by ACCU( Asia/Pacific Cultural Centre for UNESCO), Japan. He joined the Progressive Writers Association and Peoples' Theater Association as an executive. He participated many national and international level exhibitions.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/3/34/Ramkishan_Adig.jpg
